cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.CY, cs.HC, cs.DC 

The paper discusses the use of blockchain for secure and trustable management and sharing of electronic medical records (EMRs) in healthcare. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.DB (Databases), as the paper proposes a framework for managing and sharing EMR data. The paper also discusses the privacy and security concerns related to EMR data, which makes cs.CY (Computers and Society) another likely category. Additionally, cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) are also possible categories as the paper focuses on improving decision making for medical care and reducing the overall cost, which involves the use of technology and distributed systems.
